Just dinged lvl 39  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Short question.  Since Gravity Flux is an Area Effect spell, could I try to use it to quad kite?  Anyone ever try this?  I understand that I would most likely get caught up in the spell, that's the only downside.  Thanks<br>
<br>
Knotthed<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sumlain>Sumlain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(2/19/03 11:48:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gravity Flux question</span><hr size=1> to effectively quad, you'd need either snare or sow (preferrably both :-) )<br>
<br>
I haven't played with Gravity Flux a lot though so I don't know mana usage or recast delay.  It's boat loads of fun to cast on a mob that your friend the tank is fighting in an outdoor zone.  He'll be spinning around trying to figure out where the mob went and WHAM it'll land right in front of him again :-)<br>
