<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.webspan.net/~scorpio/graph/mezzed.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nagolxela>nagolxela</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(3/26/03 1:25:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gravity Flux question</span><hr size=1> It sure is fun clearing orc camps with it!<br>
<br>
I was able to park 2 mobs with root then nuke with this, but I don't suggest it.  Root duration is random, plus after they are hit with this root will most likely break.  Damage is nice, but it has a high mana cost.<br>
